ENUGU – Enugu Chamber of Commerce, Industry, Mines and Agriculture (ECCIMA) says will soon be accredited by Centre For Management Development (CMD) in order to get a functional training directorate This was disclosed by ECCIMA President elect, Jasper Nduagwuike when he paid a courtesy call to Correspondents Chapel of Nigeria Union of Journalists, Enugu chapter on Tuesday. The Commerce would soon be accredited by Centre For Management Develpoment (CMD) as a training outpost as we will have a full directorate for training. FG Plans 18 Modular Refineries In Niger Delta Lagos Govt Charges MSMEs On Capacity-Building “Already we have being certified as a training outpost and the certification of CMD is the highest certification any training outpost can ever have “The accreditation will be handed over to the chamber by 2nd of February so we will have training department where we will make available training to every sector of the economy,” He stated further that the Chamber will also have an operational directorate of marketing in order to equip its members with skills in marketing their products and service to ensure that their businesses grow. Nduagwuike who assured cordial relationship with Correspondent Chapel said “My aim is to resuscitate our relationship with correspondent chapel because there is no way the chamber can move forward without the media as there must be Cordial relationship between commerce and the media because commerce benefit from media and media benefit from commerce,” he said He attributed the problem of the annual trade fair to lack of awareness. POLL He said “The problem with our trade fair is lack of awareness because people are not well informed that there is a trade fair going on in Enugu . The responsibility of getting people to know about this rest squarely on the media but more than that, the Enugu Chamber of Commerce is on a mission of self rediscovering because before now we are not actually known as people who organize trade fairs but today unfortunately a lot of people associate us with just trade fair but that is not just what we are know for but trade fair only contribute to about only 20% of our chamber of commerce because we look after the interest of our members so we are ready to Change their beliefs. He also disclosed that the inauguration of the 16th President of the chamber will hold on 4th and 5th of February 2022. He said “the event will commence on 4th of February with welcome cocktail and dinner while the investiture holds on 5th February “The Investiture lecture will be delivered by Senator Eyinnaya Abaribe while the chairman of the occasion is Anyim Pius Anyim,” he said Responding, the Correspondent Chapel Chairman, Com Lawrence Njoku commended ECCIMA President and the team for the visit Nigeria’s Local Debt To Hit N43trn In 2022 – Agusto & Co FIRS To Prioritise Digital Economy Taxation He there assured that correspondent will continue support the Chamber in its quest to change the economy of the South East Com Njoku who said businesses in the state and region were suffering, stressed the need for ECCIMA to be at the forefront of changing the situation.